 exclusion, and samples divided for luciferase assay (2 Ã 10<sup>6</sup>
 cells/ml), flow cytometry (5 Ã 10<sup>5</sup> cells/sample), and Western
 blotting (1 Ã 10<sup>6</sup> cells/sample). Collagen was used at 10
 Î¼g/ml and rhodocytin was used at 50 n<sc>m</sc>. Luciferase activity was
